{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01EovVN91V3KQ5vvBKDQUk1h","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# F8 Plan\n2\t\n3\t## Acceptance criteria\n4\t\n5\tFrom SPEC.md §6.3 — Schema / Autocomplete:\n6\t\n7\t- `GET /api/schema` returns distinct event names and, per event, the detected property names with types.\n8\t- Response shape:\n9\t  ```json\n10\t  {\n11\t    \"event_names\": [\"Page Viewed\", \"Purchase Completed\"],\n12\t    \"properties\": {\n13\t      \"Purchase Completed\": {\n14\t        \"amount\": \"numeric\",\n15\t        \"currency\": \"string\",\n16\t        \"plan\": \"string\"\n17\t      }\n18\t    }\n19\t  }\n20\t  ```\n21\t- Computed by sampling the last 10,000 events.\n22\t- Cached in memory for 60 seconds.\n23\t\n24\tFrom SPEC.md §4.5 — Numeric property detection:\n25\t\n26\t- Numeric properties are detected at query time by attempting `JSONExtractFloat`.\n27\t- The `schema` API endpoint pre-scans a sample of recent events to return property names and inferred types, used to populate the UI dropdowns.\n28\t\n29\t## Dependencies\n30\t\n31\tCompleted features this builds on:\n32\t- F1 (`features/F1-done.md`) — ClickHouse client singleton at `src/lib/clickhouse.ts`\n33\t- F2 (`features/F2-done.md`) — Migration script; `events` table exists in ClickHouse\n34\t- F5 (`features/F5-done.md`) — `POST /api/events` route for ingesting events (needed for integration testing)\n35\t\n36\tExact file paths that will be imported or extended:\n37\t- `src/lib/clickhouse.ts` — imported for the ClickHouse client singleton\n38\t\n39\t## Files to create or modify\n40\t\n41\t- CREATE `src/lib/schema-cache.ts` — in-memory cache with 60-second TTL\n42\t- CREATE `src/app/api/schema/route.ts` — GET handler for `/api/schema`\n43\t- CREATE `src/app/api/schema/__tests__/route.test.ts` — unit tests for the route\n44\t- CREATE `src/lib/__tests__/schema-cache.test.ts` — unit tests for the cache module\n45\t\n46\t## Implementation order\n47\t\n48\t1. **Create `src/lib/schema-cache.ts`** — generic time-based in-memory cache with configurable TTL. Exports a function to get/set cached schema data and a function to invalidate/clear the cache (for testing). The cache stores the schema response and a timestamp; returns the cached value if within TTL, otherwise returns `null`.\n49\t\n50\t2. **Create `src/lib/__tests__/schema-cache.test.ts`** — unit tests for the schema cache: verifies cache hit within TTL, cache miss after TTL expiry, and manual invalidation.\n51\t\n52\t3. **Create `src/app/api/schema/route.ts`** — GET handler that:\n53\t   - Checks the schema cache; returns cached response if fresh.\n54\t   - Otherwise queries ClickHouse for distinct event names (`SELECT DISTINCT event_name FROM events ORDER BY event_name`).\n55\t   - For each event name, samples up to 10,000 recent events and extracts property keys from the `properties` JSON column using `JSONExtractKeys`.\n56\t   - For each property key, attempts `JSONExtractFloat` on a sample to determine if the property is `\"numeric\"` or `\"string\"`.\n57\t   - Assembles the response, stores it in the cache, and returns it.\n58\t\n59\t4. **Create `src/app/api/schema/__tests__/route.test.ts`** — unit tests for the route handler: verifies response shape, correct type inference, caching behavior, and empty-database edge case.\n60\t\n61\t## Sprint contract\n62\t\n63\t- [ ] File `src/lib/schema-cache.ts` exists and exports a cache mechanism (get/set/invalidate functions)\n64\t- [ ] File `src/app/api/schema/route.ts` exists and exports `GET`\n65\t- [ ] Test suite → `pnpm test` → 0 failures\n66\t- [ ] Lint check → `pnpm lint` → exit 0\n67\t- [ ] Type check → `pnpm typecheck` → exit 0\n68\t- [ ] Build check → `pnpm build` → exit 0\n69\t- [ ] HTTP check: GET `http://localhost:3000/api/schema` → response is JSON with `event_names` (array) and `properties` (object) keys\n70\t\n71\t## Test plan\n72\t\n73\t### Schema cache\n74\t\n75\t- **Test file**: `src/lib/__tests__/schema-cache.test.ts`\n76\t- **Module under test**: `src/lib/schema-cache.ts`\n77\t- **Cases to cover**:\n78\t  - Returns `null` (cache miss) when cache is empty / never set\n79\t  - Returns cached value within TTL window\n80\t  - Returns `null` (cache miss) after TTL expires (use `vi.advanceTimersByTime` or inject a clock)\n81\t  - Manual invalidation clears the cache so next get returns `null`\n82\t\n83\t### Schema route handler\n84\t\n85\t- **Test file**: `src/app/api/schema/__tests__/route.test.ts`\n86\t- **Module under test**: `src/app/api/schema/route.ts` → `GET`\n87\t- **Cases to cover**:\n88\t  - Returns 200 with `{ event_names: [], properties: {} }` when database has no events (mock ClickHouse query to return empty results)\n89\t  - Returns correct `event_names` array from distinct event names query\n90\t  - Infers `\"numeric\"` type for properties where `JSONExtractFloat` succeeds (non-zero/non-null result from ClickHouse)\n91\t  - Infers `\"string\"` type for properties where `JSONExtractFloat` returns 0/null (non-numeric values)\n92\t  - Returns cached response on second call without re-querying ClickHouse (verify mock is called only once)\n93\t  - Response shape matches spec: top-level keys are `event_names` and `properties`\n94\t\n95\t- **Integration gap**: HTTP check — GET `/api/schema` with seeded data returns populated event names and typed properties — requires dev server\n96\t\n97\t## Risks and open questions\n98\t\n99\t1. **`JSONExtractKeys` availability**: ClickHouse's `JSONExtractKeys` function extracts top-level keys from a JSON string. This is available in ClickHouse v22+. Since the spec mandates v26+ binary, this is safe.\n100\t\n101\t2. **Numeric detection heuristic**: The spec says \"attempting `JSONExtractFloat`\". A property that contains mixed types across events (e.g., `\"amount\": 49.99` in some events and `\"amount\": \"free\"` in others) needs a decision rule. The plan uses a majority/sample approach: if `JSONExtractFloat` returns a non-zero/non-null value for at least one sampled row, the property is typed as `\"numeric\"`. This matches the spec's intent of enabling numeric aggregation dropdowns — a property that is sometimes numeric is still useful for `sum`/`avg`.\n102\t\n103\t3. **Performance of per-event-name sampling**: If there are many distinct event names, running a separate sampling query per event could be slow. The implementation should use a single query that samples across all events (last 10,000 by `ingested_at` or `timestamp`), then groups property keys and types by `event_name` in application code.\n104\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1fdccd36-aa2b-42ab-a263-1d6582228471","uuid":"606655eb-bfbd-4a1f-8c38-614e4f66c2a8","timestamp":"2026-04-15T12:57:21.314Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/features/F8-plan.md","content":"# F8 Plan\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\nFrom SPEC.md §6.3 — Schema / Autocomplete:\n\n- `GET /api/schema` returns distinct event names and, per event, the detected property names with types.\n- Response shape:\n  ```json\n  {\n    \"event_names\": [\"Page Viewed\", \"Purchase Completed\"],\n    \"properties\": {\n      \"Purchase Completed\": {\n        \"amount\": \"numeric\",\n        \"currency\": \"string\",\n        \"plan\": \"string\"\n      }\n    }\n  }\n  ```\n- Computed by sampling the last 10,000 events.\n- Cached in memory for 60 seconds.\n\nFrom SPEC.md §4.5 — Numeric property detection:\n\n- Numeric properties are detected at query time by attempting `JSONExtractFloat`.\n- The `schema` API endpoint pre-scans a sample of recent events to return property names and inferred types, used to populate the UI dropdowns.\n\n## Dependencies\n\nCompleted features this builds on:\n- F1 (`features/F1-done.md`) — ClickHouse client singleton at `src/lib/clickhouse.ts`\n- F2 (`features/F2-done.md`) — Migration script; `events` table exists in ClickHouse\n- F5 (`features/F5-done.md`) — `POST /api/events` route for ingesting events (needed for integration testing)\n\nExact file paths that will be imported or extended:\n- `src/lib/clickhouse.ts` — imported for the ClickHouse client singleton\n\n## Files to create or modify\n\n- CREATE `src/lib/schema-cache.ts` — in-memory cache with 60-second TTL\n- CREATE `src/app/api/schema/route.ts` — GET handler for `/api/schema`\n- CREATE `src/app/api/schema/__tests__/route.test.ts` — unit tests for the route\n- CREATE `src/lib/__tests__/schema-cache.test.ts` — unit tests for the cache module\n\n## Implementation order\n\n1. **Create `src/lib/schema-cache.ts`** — generic time-based in-memory cache with configurable TTL. Exports a function to get/set cached schema data and a function to invalidate/clear the cache (for testing). The cache stores the schema response and a timestamp; returns the cached value if within TTL, otherwise returns `null`.\n\n2. **Create `src/lib/__tests__/schema-cache.test.ts`** — unit tests for the schema cache: verifies cache hit within TTL, cache miss after TTL expiry, and manual invalidation.\n\n3. **Create `src/app/api/schema/route.ts`** — GET handler that:\n   - Checks the schema cache; returns cached response if fresh.\n   - Otherwise queries ClickHouse for distinct event names (`SELECT DISTINCT event_name FROM events ORDER BY event_name`).\n   - For each event name, samples up to 10,000 recent events and extracts property keys from the `properties` JSON column using `JSONExtractKeys`.\n   - For each property key, attempts `JSONExtractFloat` on a sample to determine if the property is `\"numeric\"` or `\"string\"`.\n   - Assembles the response, stores it in the cache, and returns it.\n\n4. **Create `src/app/api/schema/__tests__/route.test.ts`** — unit tests for the route handler: verifies response shape, correct type inference, caching behavior, and empty-database edge case.\n\n## Sprint contract\n\n- [ ] File `src/lib/schema-cache.ts` exists and exports a cache mechanism (get/set/invalidate functions)\n- [ ] File `src/app/api/schema/route.ts` exists and exports `GET`\n- [ ] Test suite → `pnpm test` → 0 failures\n- [ ] Lint check → `pnpm lint` → exit 0\n- [ ] Type check → `pnpm typecheck` → exit 0\n- [ ] Build check → `pnpm build` → exit 0\n- [ ] HTTP check: GET `http://localhost:3000/api/schema` → response is JSON with `event_names` (array) and `properties` (object) keys\n\n## Test plan\n\n### Schema cache\n\n- **Test file**: `src/lib/__tests__/schema-cache.test.ts`\n- **Module under test**: `src/lib/schema-cache.ts`\n- **Cases to cover**:\n  - Returns `null` (cache miss) when cache is empty / never set\n  - Returns cached value within TTL window\n  - Returns `null` (cache miss) after TTL expires (use `vi.advanceTimersByTime` or inject a clock)\n  - Manual invalidation clears the cache so next get returns `null`\n\n### Schema route handler\n\n- **Test file**: `src/app/api/schema/__tests__/route.test.ts`\n- **Module under test**: `src/app/api/schema/route.ts` → `GET`\n- **Cases to cover**:\n  - Returns 200 with `{ event_names: [], properties: {} }` when database has no events (mock ClickHouse query to return empty results)\n  - Returns correct `event_names` array from distinct event names query\n  - Infers `\"numeric\"` type for properties where `JSONExtractFloat` succeeds (non-zero/non-null result from ClickHouse)\n  - Infers `\"string\"` type for properties where `JSONExtractFloat` returns 0/null (non-numeric values)\n  - Returns cached response on second call without re-querying ClickHouse (verify mock is called only once)\n  - Response shape matches spec: top-level keys are `event_names` and `properties`\n\n- **Integration gap**: HTTP check — GET `/api/schema` with seeded data returns populated event names and typed properties — requires dev server\n\n## Risks and open questions\n\n1. **`JSONExtractKeys` availability**: ClickHouse's `JSONExtractKeys` function extracts top-level keys from a JSON string. This is available in ClickHouse v22+. Since the spec mandates v26+ binary, this is safe.\n\n2. **Numeric detection heuristic**: The spec says \"attempting `JSONExtractFloat`\". A property that contains mixed types across events (e.g., `\"amount\": 49.99` in some events and `\"amount\": \"free\"` in others) needs a decision rule. The plan uses a majority/sample approach: if `JSONExtractFloat` returns a non-zero/non-null value for at least one sampled row, the property is typed as `\"numeric\"`. This matches the spec's intent of enabling numeric aggregation dropdowns — a property that is sometimes numeric is still useful for `sum`/`avg`.\n\n3. **Performance of per-event-name sampling**: If there are many distinct event names, running a separate sampling query per event could be slow. The implementation should use a single query that samples across all events (last 10,000 by `ingested_at` or `timestamp`), then groups property keys and types by `event_name` in application code.\n","numLines":104,"startLine":1,"totalLines":104}}}
